law.history: Repealed, effective March 23, 1998, 1996 Ky. Acts ch. 365, sec. 64, effective upon contingency; contingent effective date repealed 1998 Ky. Acts ch. 101, sec. 20, effective March 23, 1998. -- Created 1972 Ky. Acts ch. 158, sec. 3.

metadata.catchline-at-repeal: Extradition -- Governor may require Commonwealth's attorney to investigate before demand.
